items.title: Bellinger helps cut LA's magic number to 7
items.summary: Cody Bellinger homered and drove in three runs Wednesday as the Dodgers conducted their first dress rehearsal for October in a 4-1 triumph over the Giants.

items.title: Leake provides boost to Mariners' rotation
items.summary: Mike Leake took a different path this time, but the end result was another Mariners win -- an 8-1 victory over the Rangers -- and that worked quite well for the newest Seattle starter on Wednesday night at Globe Life Park.

items.title: Would potential playoff rotation include Fister?
items.summary: For the Red Sox, one of the most intriguing storylines during the final stretch of the regular season is the race for the final spots in the rotation heading into a potential American League Division Series against the Astros or Indians.

items.title: Suarez's slam costly after Cardinals' miscues
items.summary: Eugenio Suarez's grand slam may have been the final blow in a five-run fifth inning for the Reds that sent the Cardinals to a 6-0 loss on Wednesday night, but it was a play and pitch not executed that pushed the inning deep enough for things to unravel.

items.title: Gohara leaves nerves, walks behind for 1st W
items.summary: Luiz Gohara admits that nerves may have gotten the best of him when he made his big league debut last week against the Rangers. But in Wednesday's 8-2 win over the Nationals, the 21-year-old lefty showed the Braves exactly why many think he has promising upside.
